HEADWORD: Tetractinellida
<hw>Te*trac`ti*nel"li*da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., from Gr. <grk>te`tra-</grk> tetra- + <?/, <?/, ray,
spoke.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of Spongiae in which
the spicules are siliceous and have four branches diverging at right
angles. Called also <altname>Tetractinellinae</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

